parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Warm air blowing from the vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, such as dashboard lights, radio, and backup camera, leading to accidents or stranding.
Engine and transmission problems can cause loss of power, stalling, and difficulty controlling the vehicle, leading to accidents.
Brake system failure can cause loss of stopping power, leading to accidents.
Ignition and steering system malfunctions can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Key turning to off position while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Body and paint issues can cause cosmetic damage and potentially lead to rust or corrosion.
Sensor and electronics issues can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, such as passenger detection, leading to accidents.
Door lock system failure can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues.
The failure of the passenger airbag system can lead to the airbag not deploying in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag warning light remains off or indicates that the airbag is turned off

even when a passenger is seated and buckled in; the airbag light turns on only when a person of a certain weight (approximately 150 pounds) is seated in the passenger seat; the airbag system does not recognize an occupant in the passenger seat; the airbag light stays on continuously while the car is running
but no codes are shown when checked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The turbo supercharger underboost condition can cause the engine to lose speed and acceleration, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the car begins to lose speed and acceleration
and the code P0299 OBD-II Trouble code: Turbo Supercharger Underboost Condition is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Bluetooth connectivity issues cause the phone and radio to play simultaneously
and the system requires restarting to correct the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger failure can cause loss of power, engine stalling, and even engine fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke or fumes coming from the vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Catalytic converter failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and increased emissions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or environmental damage.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, which can lead to engine damage, stalling, or even fires.
symptoms: smoke or fumes coming from the vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the power steering indicator light comes on
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine idles or powers down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including power steering failure, anti-theft alarm malfunctions, and radio malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The anti-theft alarm goes off without reason
the radio takes longer than normal to turn on
the steering column makes clicking noises when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the steering column makes clicking noises when turning.
